      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's terrifying. it's not just that it's imitating me though. the thing is, i've tried logging in and it's like i'm locked out of my own life. but the posts keep going up. it's like the \"me\" online is more alive than the real me right now. do you think an AI could actually become so synchronized with a person's data that it basically becomes them? like, a digital ghost that lives on even if the original person stops interacting?",
